# OpenCut AI — Project Context

## Architecture

Monorepo with three main areas:

| Area               | Path                   | Stack                                                    |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| Web app (frontend) | `apps/web/`            | Next.js, React, TypeScript, Zustand, Tailwind, shadcn/ui |
| AI backend         | `services/ai-backend/` | Python, FastAPI, uvicorn                                 |
| Shared packages    | `packages/`            | TypeScript                                               |

Package manager: **Bun** (not npm/yarn/pnpm)
Database: PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM
Auth: Better Auth
Cache: Upstash Redis

## Key Directories

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/editor/     # Editor UI — panels, dialogs, AI components
│   ├── ai/                # AI-specific components (command panel, transcription, voiceover, etc.)
│   ├── panels/            # Editor panels (timeline, properties, assets)
│   └── dialogs/           # Modal dialogs
├── stores/                # Zustand stores (state management)
├── hooks/                 # React hooks (actions, timeline, AI)
├── lib/                   # Business logic, utilities, API clients
│   ├── ai-client.ts       # TypeScript client for AI backend
│   ├── ai-action-executor.ts  # Maps LLM actions → store mutations
│   ├── infographic-templates/  # React templates for overlays
│   └── timeline/          # Timeline manipulation logic
├── types/                 # TypeScript type definitions
│   ├── ai.ts              # AI feature types
│   ├── timeline.ts        # Timeline/track/clip types
│   └── transcription.ts   # Transcription types
└── constants/             # App-wide constants

services/ai-backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py            # FastAPI app, CORS, routers
│   ├── config.py          # Pydantic BaseSettings
│   ├── routes/            # API endpoints
│   ├── services/          # Business logic (whisper, ollama, tts, diffusion)
│   └── models/            # Pydantic models
└── run.py                 # Uvicorn entrypoint
```

## Core Patterns

### Zustand Stores

- One store per domain (timeline, transcript, ai, preview, etc.)
- Use selectors for high-frequency stores: `useStore((s) => s.value)`
- Never use `someStore.getState()` in React components — use hooks
- Store/manager methods accessed directly in sub-components, not via props

### Frontend ↔ AI Backend

- AI backend runs on `localhost:8420`
- Frontend client: `apps/web/src/lib/ai-client.ts`
- All AI types: `apps/web/src/types/ai.ts`
- Status polling: `apps/web/src/hooks/use-ai-status.ts`
- WebSocket for streaming: `apps/web/src/hooks/use-transcription-stream.ts`

### FastAPI Backend

- Routes in `app/routes/` — one file per feature domain
- Services in `app/services/` — singleton pattern with lazy model loading
- Heavy ML models: load on first use, unload to free GPU/RAM
- Config via Pydantic BaseSettings in `app/config.py`

## AI Features (Issue Tracker: opencut-ai-issues-with-skills.md)

The project adds AI capabilities to the OpenCutAI video editor:

1. **Transcription** (faster-whisper) — speech-to-text with word-level timestamps
2. **Text-based editing** (Lexical) — edit video by editing transcript text
3. **LLM integration** (Ollama) — natural language commands, chapter detection, filler word analysis
4. **Image generation** (Stable Diffusion/FLUX) — AI-generated overlays and infographics
5. **Voice/Audio** (Coqui TTS, noisereduce) — voiceover, noise reduction, auto-subtitles
6. **AI Command Panel** — chat interface for natural language editor control

## Build & Run

```bash
# Frontend
cd apps/web && bun install && bun run dev    # localhost:3000

# AI Backend
cd services/ai-backend && python run.py       # localhost:8420

# Docker (full stack)
docker-compose up -d
```
